title: Jeffrey A. Rosen
added: Rosen is reported to have guided numerous initiatives, including an antitrust review of online technology platforms, criminal and civil opioids enforcement and legislation, investigations and prosecutions of IP theft and of cyberhacking, counter-UAS measures to facilitate safe use of drones, redress of pandemic-related fraud, and reform of regulatory and administrative law, among others. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Shepherson |first1=David |title=Acting AG Rosen stepping down as Trump administration ends |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-justice/acting-ag-rosen-stepping-down-as-trump-administration-ends-idUSKBN29P1EU |website=Reuters |publisher=Reuters |access-date=23 March 2021}}</ref> Drawing from his previous role as Deputy Secretary of Transportation, Rosen raised concerns about foreign made drones and the implications they have on data and cyber security. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Heavy |first1=Susan |last2=Stone |first2=Mike |title=U.S. Justice Department seeks to curb risks of foreign-made drones |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-drones/u-s-justice-department-seeks-to-curb-risks-of-foreign-made-drones-idUSKBN26T3D2 |website=Reuters |publisher=Reuters |access-date=23 March 2021}}</ref>
